<HEADLINE>
OFFICIALS QUELL RIOT OF 200 AT TENT JAIL
</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)   By RACHEL OCHOA  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHOENIX _ Two hundred inmates at Tent City Jail rioted Saturday
night, hurling rocks at officers, lighting fires to six tents and
dumping over portable toilets.
</P>
<P>
   No one was injured, and no one escaped in the ``bedtime''
disturb ance at the Maricopa County jail, which ended about an hour
after officers used pepper spray on the rampagers, said Sgt. Dave
Trombi, a Sheriff's Office spokesman.
</P>
<P>
   ``This was dealt with real quick,'' Trombi said.
</P>
<P>
   More than 200 Phoenix police officers, sheriff's deputies and
Phoenix firefighters also responded to the riot, Sheriff Joe Arpaio
said Saturday at the scene.
</P>
<P>
   Arpaio said it was probably gang-related and began about 9 p.m.
as inmates were listening to their bedtime story of Star Wars, part
of a new program.
</P>
<P>
   With their faces hidden behind tow els, rioters lit mattresses,
trash cans and six tents on fire, but none of the tents was
destroyed, said Capt. David Wilson, a special projects commander.
</P>
<P>
   Matches are considered contra band, but Wilson said the public
sometimes throws cigarettes and matches over the fence.
</P>
<P>
   Trombi said officers had noted that tension, possibly racially
moti vated, was stirring among the inmates Friday and contributed
to Saturday's flare-up.
</P>
<P>
   On Saturday night, instead of getting ready for story time, many
milled about outside the tents.
</P>
<P>
   About 100 inmates were moved late Saturday to other ``hard
jail'' facilities, such as Durango and Madison Street, and 35
``instiga tors'' were moved to the Towers Jail, Arpaio and Trombi
said.
</P>
<P>
   In noting the response time, Arpaio made reference to a 1996
riot, saying, ``We have learned something about this disturbance.''
</P>
<P>
   On Nov. 17, 1996, hundreds of inmates, angry over conditions in
Tent City, rioted after an inmate went to a toilet without
permission and was pepper-sprayed by a guard. Three guards and six
inmates were injured.
</P>
<P>
   Three guards patrolling the jail quickly were overmatched by hun
dreds of rioters, some armed with sledgehammers. Guards in the Es
trella Jail complex that includes Tent City didn't have access to
helmets, gas masks and other riot gear.
</P>
<P>
   Several fires erupted, and Na tional Guard troops were seen
entering.
</P>
<P>
   After the riot was quelled, Arpaio promised to let an inmates
commit tee air complaints of abusive guards, bad food and poor
living conditions. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
