   COMPUTERS-BIOLOGY (San Francisco) _ In a world where computers
were once casual and isolated tools, but are today increasingly the
very fabric of modern business life, computer researchers say they
are detecting an ominous trend toward programs that mimic viruses
and pestilence in the physical world. Like biological diseases,
which exploit the most basic mechanism of life: the power of DNA to
replicate itself, the subculture of modern virus writing is now
manipulating that same power within the world of interconnected
computers. By John Markoff.
