<HEADLINE>
TREASURY AND OTHER DEBT OFFERINGS ARE SCHEDULED 
</HEADLINE>
  (Eds: The words PLUS and MINUS in parentheses have been used
instead of the symbols, which are non-transmittable to many
newspaper systems.) 
(lb) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Treasury's schedule of financings this week is confined to
Monday's regular weekly auction of three- and six-month bills.
</P>
<P>
   By the close of the New York cash market on Friday, traders
said, the rate on the outstanding three-month bill was 4.59 percent
and a six-month bill was 4.87 percent.
</P>
<P>
   The following taxable and tax-exempt fixed-income issues are
scheduled for pricing this week:
</P>
<P>
   TAXABLE
</P>
<P>
   ONE DAY DURING THE WEEK
</P>
<P>
   AES Ironwood, $322 million of projected finance of debt
securities, Baa3/BBB(MINUS)/---. Lehman Brothers.
</P>
<P>
   Chiquita Brands International Inc., approximately $203 million
in two parts: U.S. $125 million of senior notes due 2009,
---/---/---. Lehman Brothers and Salomon Smith Barney and Euro 75
million of senior notes due 2009, ---/---/---. Salomon Smith Barney
and Warburg, Dillon Read &AMP; Co.
</P>
<P>
   Diageo PLC, $1 billion of 5-year global notes, A1/A(PLUS)/---.
Goldman, Sachs &AMP; Co.
</P>
