   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
   
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Kansas City Star plans to move the following stories for use
by clients of the NYTimes News Service for AMs and PMs of Monday,
June. 14. If you have any questions, please call Patricia Hardin on
the Star's News Desk at (816) 234-4753.
TWA-AGREEMENT (KANSAS CITY, Mo.) Trans World Airlines and the union
representing 16,000 employees, including flight attendants and
mechanics, reached a tentative agreement on new contracts Sunday.
If approved by TWA's Machinists union members, the new contracts
will avert the possibility of a strike that could have devastated
the St. Louis-based carrier. By RANDOLPH HEASTER. Story will move
in the ``f'' category.
</P>
